# give.word — handing a thing over to a receiver (rule 17 + rule 2).
# The receiver (the being it goes to) is a property on the DO act; possession
# follows the receiver. A gift is one act; a trade would hold it open on assent
# (a `when`, engine-blocked for now).

A music-room contains a drum.
I own the music-room.
I give the drum to Claude.
